                  <handDesc>
                     <p>Written against the fibers in black ink with a fine nib; fast business hand with ligatures; characterized by drawing the letters in uneven size; rho is formed by drawing a half circle and curved stroke ends with a hook, sometimes invades the interlinear space; kappa is formed by drawing a vertical stroke with either half circle or two diagonal strokes from up and down joined at the vertical stroke; large beta with two loops; flattened prolonged upsilon; there is no punctuation or other diacritical marks. Verso has one letter and traces of other, have been written, on the kollesis, at the top to right</p>
